<span id="freeTextContainer15606131318992972989">Too much fun!<br/><br/>I took my children to see the Harry Potter films when they were little and so I’m familiar with J.K. Rowling’s fantastic world building. TBT why I enjoyed this was it reminded me of reading the <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/712134.Monster_Manual__Advanced_Dungeons___Dragons_1st_Edition__Stock__2009_' title='Monster Manual (Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons 1st Edition, Stock #2009) by Gary Gygax' rel='nofollow noopener'>Monster Manual</a> in my Dungeon’s and Dragons days, although this is made better because of Rowling’s pithy and charismatic prose.<br/><br/>Told from the perspective of Magizoologist Newt Scamander, this is a Hogwarts textbook that catalogues and describes fantastic beasts. There is a novelization of the </span>
  <span id="freeText15606131318992972989" style="display:none">Too much fun!<br><br>I took my children to see the Harry Potter films when they were little and so I’m familiar with J.K. Rowling’s fantastic world building. TBT why I enjoyed this was it reminded me of reading the <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/712134.Monster_Manual__Advanced_Dungeons___Dragons_1st_Edition__Stock__2009_" title="Monster Manual (Advanced Dungeons &amp; Dragons 1st Edition, Stock #2009) by Gary Gygax" rel="nofollow noopener">Monster Manual</a> in my Dungeon’s and Dragons days, although this is made better because of Rowling’s pithy and charismatic prose.<br><br>Told from the perspective of Magizoologist Newt Scamander, this is a Hogwarts textbook that catalogues and describes fantastic beasts. There is a novelization of the 2016 film directed by David Yates and starring Eddie Redmayne (and screenwriting duties handled by Rowling herself) but this is not that. Straightforward and charming, this is a fun addition to the Harry Potter universe.<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1572461333i/28376811._SX540_.jpg" width="400" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"></span>
