<div id="review_2590505958" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2590505958" />
    <a title="Meags" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8542123-meags"><img alt="Meags" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611612238p2/8542123.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2590505958?book_show_action=true">Nov 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Meags" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Meags" href="/user/show/8542123-meags">Meags</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/32328260-fantastic-beasts-and-where-to-find-them">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8542123-meags?shelf=magic">magic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8542123-meags?shelf=borrowbox">borrowbox</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8542123-meags?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2590505958" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15225663965923026215"><b>4 Stars</b><br/><br/>Newt Scamander’s encyclopaedia of magical creatures was a fun and fascinating little read.<br/><br/>Rowling’s imagination never ceases to amaze me. I doubt I’ll ever tire of reading stories set in the brilliance of the Potterverse - seriously, keep ‘em coming!<br/><br/>I highly recommend the audio edition of this story which was narrated by the talented Eddie Redmayne.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


